INFO:argostranslate.utils:('paragraphs:', ['a fixed, pre-trained reconstructor P \u03d5 ( q | ЁЄ ) , which serves as a tractable approximation to the inverse mapping G . However, naively maximizing log P \u03d5 ( q | Іг ) can lead to degenerate solutions in which the agent encodes q into the action sequence through trivial lexical copying (e.g., by repeating the question in a search query or partially restating it in the final response for context), allowing the reconstructor to recover q without relying on the search results. To mitigate this issue, we introduce a bottleneck transformation Із : T Ёњ \u02dc T and optimize the following objective: ІШ \u2217 = argmax ІШ E q \u223cD , Іг \u223c Іа ІШ ( ЁЄ| q ) \x02 log P \u03d5 \x00 q | Із ( Іг ) \x01\x03 . (3) 3.3 Strategic Information Bottlenecks The transformation function Із imposes structural constraints on the trajectory so that it retains the search scaffold while reducing lexical shortcuts that would otherwise allow trivial reconstruction of the source question. We define Із as the composition of two operations: final response exclusion and entity masking : Із = Із mask \u25e6 Із trace . Final response exclusion. We first address leakage through the final response. In standard QA interactions, the final response a T often paraphrases q to provide context. Including it in the reconstruction input can bypass the evaluation of the search process.'])
