INFO:argostranslate.utils:('paragraphs:', ['For each question q , the agent samples a group of G trajectories { Іг 1 , Іг 2 , . . . , Іг G } from the current policy Іа ІШ old . For each Іг i , we compute a reconstructed question \u02c6 q i \u223c P \u03d5 ( ЁЄ | Із ( Іг i )) and define the reward as the semantic similarity between q and \u02c6 q i : r ( Іг i ) = Sim \x00 E ( q ) , E (\u02c6 q i ) \x01 , (5) where E ( ЁЄ ) is a sentence embedding function and Sim( ЁЄ , ЁЄ ) denotes cosine similarity. We then compute an advantage A i by normalizing rewards within the group: A i = r ( Іг i ) \u2212 ІЬ ( { r ( Іг j ) } G j =1 ) Ів ( { r ( Іг j ) } G j =1 ) + \u03f5 , (6) where ІЬ and Ів denote the mean and standard deviation of group rewards. The GRPO objective is then: L GRP O ( ІШ ) = E q \u223cD " 1 G G X i =1 \x10 min \x10 Іа ІШ ( Іг i | q ) Іа ІШ old ( Іг i | q ) A i , clip \x10 Іа ІШ ( Іг i | q ) Іа ІШ old ( Іг i | q ) , 1 \u2212 \u03f5, 1 + \u03f5 \x11 A i \x11 \u2212 ІТ D KL ( Іа ІШ ЁЮ Іа ref ) \x11 # . (7) Here, observations are treated as environment outputs and Іа ІШ ( Іг i | q ) refers to the likelihood of the agent- generated tokens/actions (Jin et al., 2025a). This objective increases the likelihood of trajectories that yield higher reconstruction fidelity relative to the group average, thereby encouraging search behaviors that better preserve the structure and information needed to recover the original question. 4 Experiments We empirically evaluate Cycle-Consistent Search (CCS) across a diverse range of knowledge-intensive tasks.'])
INFO:argostranslate.utils:('apply_packaged_translation', 'For each question q , the agent samples a group of G trajectories { Іг 1 , Іг 2 , . . . , Іг G } from the current policy Іа ІШ old . For each Іг i , we compute a reconstructed question \u02c6 q i \u223c P \u03d5 ( ЁЄ | Із ( Іг i )) and define the reward as the semantic similarity between q and \u02c6 q i : r ( Іг i ) = Sim \x00 E ( q ) , E (\u02c6 q i ) \x01 , (5) where E ( ЁЄ ) is a sentence embedding function and Sim( ЁЄ , ЁЄ ) denotes cosine similarity. We then compute an advantage A i by normalizing rewards within the group: A i = r ( Іг i ) \u2212 ІЬ ( { r ( Іг j ) } G j =1 ) Ів ( { r ( Іг j ) } G j =1 ) + \u03f5 , (6) where ІЬ and Ів denote the mean and standard deviation of group rewards. The GRPO objective is then: L GRP O ( ІШ ) = E q \u223cD " 1 G G X i =1 \x10 min \x10 Іа ІШ ( Іг i | q ) Іа ІШ old ( Іг i | q ) A i , clip \x10 Іа ІШ ( Іг i | q ) Іа ІШ old ( Іг i | q ) , 1 \u2212 \u03f5, 1 + \u03f5 \x11 A i \x11 \u2212 ІТ D KL ( Іа ІШ ЁЮ Іа ref ) \x11 # . (7) Here, observations are treated as environment outputs and Іа ІШ ( Іг i | q ) refers to the likelihood of the agent- generated tokens/actions (Jin et al., 2025a). This objective increases the likelihood of trajectories that yield higher reconstruction fidelity relative to the group average, thereby encouraging search behaviors that better preserve the structure and information needed to recover the original question. 4 Experiments We empirically evaluate Cycle-Consistent Search (CCS) across a diverse range of knowledge-intensive tasks.')
